column1: # Definition: Measures the total % of people who have access to Improved sanitation facilities, which include: flush or pour-flush to piped sewer system, septic tank or pit latrine; ventilated improved pit latrine; pit latrine with slab; and composting toilet.
# Source: WHO/UNICEF Joint Monitoring Programme for Water Supply and Sanitation
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
